SIMPLE: initiatory
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Initiatory
<hw>In*i"ti*a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Suitable for an introduction or beginning; introductory; prefatory;
<as>as, an <ex>initiatory</ex> step</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tending or serving to initiate; introducing by
instruction, or by the use and application of symbols or ceremonies;
elementary; rudimentary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some <qex>initiatory</qex> treatises in the law.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two <qex>initiatory</qex> rites of the same general import can not
exist together.</q> <rj><qau>J. M. Mason.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Initiatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Initiatory
<hw>In*i"ti*a*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An introductory act or
rite.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inition</ent>⟦br⟧
